  "texts": [
    "Wen et al. [7] proposed DiLu, a framework that instills knowledge-driven capability into autonomous driving using LLMs.",
    "DiLu takes scene description vectors x V sd as input and outputs acceleration a Aacc, idle a A id, and decelerate a A dec actions.",
    "Fu et al. [44] explored the use of LLMs for human-like autonomous driving, taking environment observations x Oe and generating discrete meta actions a Am.Interpretability and explainability have also been addressed by researchers.",
    "Wang et al. [43] introduced DriveMLM, an LLM-based autonomous driving framework that aligns LLM decisions with the behavioral planning module.",
    "DriveMLM takes multi-modal inputs, such as images x I, point clouds x P, traffic rules x Tr, system messages x Sm, and user instructions x Ui, and generates decision states a Ds and explanations a E. Han et al. [48] proposed DME-Driver, a system that emulates interpretable decision-making and control using a powerful vision-language model, taking current and previous scene images x Ic, x Ip, prompts x P, and vehicle status x Sv as inputs, and generating human-like logic a L h, focus areas a Fa, scene descriptions a Ds, reasoning a R, decisions a D, and control signals a Cs.Other notable contributions include Agent-Driver by Mao et al."
